Author: Liquid_Is_A_Paper
Text: Nope. That's below maintenance for like 99% of people, and whilst you may get some water weight if this is the first time you've eaten properly in a while, it's not body fat.   1100+ calories is the normal amount, what you're supposed to eat to be healthy, so the idea that it's going to cause sudden rapid weight gain is just an ED lie.
